Ing '''Ayang lalaki''' ('''''Amaranthus spinosus'''''), ausan deng '''spiny amaranth''', '''prickly amaranth''' o '''thorny amaranth''' king Ingles, ampong '''kulitis''' king Tagalug. Katutubu ya o natibu king malisangan nang dake ning Americas ([[Pangulung America|Pangulung]] ampong [[Mauling America]]) (''native to the tropical Americas''), oneng atyu kareng anggang continenti antimong species a midala (''introduced species''), at neng kai, marok a dikut a maragul perwisyu (''noxious weed''). Maragul ing darala nang kasiran kareng asikan a pitatamnan [[pale]] king [[Asia]]. <ref>{{cite book|title=A practical field guide to weeds of rice in Asia |author=Caton, B. P. |author2=M. Mortimer |author3=J. E. Hill  |url=http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=ver3qCQF9EEC&printsec=frontcover&dq=field+guide&hl=en&ei=DjywTLzQGYiBOvyFgIwG&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=6&ved=0CEYQ6AEwBTgK#v=onepage&q&f=false |year=2004 |pages=20â€“21 |publisher=International Rice Research Institute }}</ref>

